I use this with [[SWFObject]]:

<pre class="sh_javascript">
var so = new SWFObject("myswf.swf", "mymovie2", "120", "50", "10", "#FFFFFF");
so.addParam("wmode","transparent");
so.addParam("scale","noborder");
so.addParam("salign","right");
so.write("target");
</pre>

If the [[SWF]] movie is 220x50, in my experience, only the right part of the 220px wide will display.

The important parts are:
<pre class="sh_javascript">
so.addParam("scale","noborder");
so.addParam("salign","right");
</pre>

